\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces RQ1 headline: month-over-month incumbent ranking stability (Kendall $\tau _b$, incumbents with $\geq 1000$ votes) for BT and the lattice link across all thirteen refit windows. The two curves are statistically indistinguishable---median paired difference $+0.00000$, with five windows exactly tied---while both improve together as the pool matures, from $\tau _b \approx 0.97$ to $\approx 0.997$. Source: \texttt  {rq1\_metrics.csv}.}}{7}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:rq1}{{2}{7}{RQ1 headline: month-over-month incumbent ranking stability (Kendall $\tau _b$, incumbents with $\geq 1000$ votes) for BT and the lattice link across all thirteen refit windows. The two curves are statistically indistinguishable---median paired difference $+0.00000$, with five windows exactly tied---while both improve together as the pool matures, from $\tau _b \approx 0.97$ to $\approx 0.997$. Source: \texttt {rq1\_metrics.csv}}{figure.2}{}}
